  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Deseed the<strong> red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/623_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/623_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/623_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/623_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/623_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced&nbsp;</strong><strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sliced&nbsp;onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;pepper</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>sugar&nbsp;</strong>and cook for 10 min, or until everything has softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/623_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/623_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/623_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/623_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/623_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 175ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
